<node CREATED="1166202715280" ID="Freemind_Link_1074698023" MODIFIED="1166202834266" TEXT="ENEE 731: Image Understanding (Fall 2006)\\&#xa;End-Semester Exam">
<node CREATED="1166202837060" FOLDED="true" ID="_" MODIFIED="1166202844818" POSITION="right" TEXT="Problem 1">
<node CREATED="1166202864581" ID="Freemind_Link_1399118939" MODIFIED="1166211713405" TEXT="\begin{proof} If the distance between camera centers is $2s$, then the locations of the camera centers $C_l,C_r$ are $[-s, 0, 0]$ and $[s, 0, 0]$.  Assuming the camera viewing axes are parallel with the z axis of the 3-D point $\mathbf{X}$ in the canonical coordinate system is therefore related to points $\mathbf{X_l}$ and $\mathbf{X_r}$ in the camera coordinate systems by:&#xa;$$\mathbf{X_l}=\mathbf{X}-C_l$$&#xa;$$\mathbf{X_r}=\mathbf{X}-C_r$$&#xa;Since only the $X$ coordinate is affected, $Y_l=Y_r, Z_l=Z_r$ and these equation reduce to:&#xa;$$X_l=X+s$$&#xa;$$X_r=X-s$$&#xa;Assuming a perspective projection with focal length $f$, points in the images ($\mathbf{x_l},\mathbf{x_r}$) are related to points in the camera view by:&#xa;$$X_l = \frac{x_l Z}{f}$$&#xa;$$Y_l = \frac{y_l Z}{f}$$&#xa;and similarly for $\mathbf{X_r}$ and $\mathbf{x_r}$.\\&#xa;Substituting for $X_l,X_r$ in the equations above:&#xa;$$\frac{x_l Z}{f} = X + s$$&#xa;$$\frac{x_r Z}{f} = X - s$$&#xa;Subtracting the bottom from the top equation:&#xa;$$\frac{Z}{f}(x_l-x_r) = 2s$$&#xa;Solving for $Z$:&#xa;$$Z = \frac{2sf}{x_l-x_r}$$&#xa;Relative error is defined as $\frac{\delta{x}}{x} = \frac{x_0 - x}{x}$, where $x$ is the true value and $x_0$ is the measured value.&#xa;The relative error for $Z$ in the above equation is:&#xa;\begin{eqnarray*}&#xa;\frac{Z_0 - Z}{Z} &amp;=&amp; \frac{ \left(\frac{2sf}{x_{l0} - x_{r0}}\right) - \left(\frac{2sf}{x_l - x_r}\right)}&#xa;{\frac{2sf}{x_l - x_r}}\\&#xa;&amp;=&amp; \frac{ (x_{l0}-x_{r0}) - (x_l - x_r) }{ (x_l - x_r) }\\&#xa;\frac{\delta{Z}}{Z}&amp;=&amp; \frac{\delta(x_l-x_r)}{x_l-x_r}&#xa;\end{eqnarray*}&#xa;\end{proof}&#xa;Shows the negative of what I was supposed to show?"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1166202846801" FOLDED="true" ID="Freemind_Link_721482104" MODIFIED="1166202849499" POSITION="right" TEXT="Problem 2">
<node CREATED="1166207643321" ID="Freemind_Link_1756272627" MODIFIED="1166207645924" TEXT="%">
<node CREATED="1166207103341" ID="Freemind_Link_648396735" MODIFIED="1166207544488" TEXT="\newtheorem*{part_a}{Part a}&#xa;\begin{part_a}&#xa;\textbf{Claim:} If the surface being imaged is a plane described by:\\&#xa;$$Z=Z_0+pX+qY$$\\&#xa;where $X,Y,$ and $Z$ are coordinates of points on the surface, then\\&#xa;$$\frac{Z_0}{Z} = 1 - px - qy$$&#xa;\end{part_a}"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1166206438861" ID="Freemind_Link_267323994" MODIFIED="1166207801756" TEXT="\begin{proof}[Proof of (a)]&#xa;Given:&#xa;$$Z=Z_0 + pX + qY$$\\&#xa;Assuming a perspective projection with focal length $f$: \\&#xa;$$X=\frac{xZ}{f},Y=\frac{yZ}{f}$$\\&#xa;Substituting:\\&#xa;$$Z = Z_0 + \frac{pxZ}{f}+\frac{qyZ}{f}$$\\&#xa;Shifting terms:\\&#xa;$$Z_0 = \frac{Z}{f} \cdot \left(1 - px - qy)\right)$$\\&#xa;Assuming $f=1$, :\\&#xa;$$\frac{Z_0}{Z}=1-px-qy$$&#xa;\end{proof}"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1166202850161" ID="Freemind_Link_1271714971" MODIFIED="1166202852095" POSITION="right" TEXT="Problem 3"/>
<node CREATED="1166202852841" FOLDED="true" ID="Freemind_Link_604277903" MODIFIED="1166202854978" POSITION="right" TEXT="Problem 4">
<node CREATED="1166301382702" ID="Freemind_Link_712593390" MODIFIED="1166307605704" TEXT="The finite difference approximation for the second partial derivatives of a 2D function $f$ are as follows:&#xa;$$f_{xx}=f(x+1,y)-2f(x)+f(x-1,y)$$&#xa;$$f_{yy}=f(x,y+1)-2f(x)+f(x,y-1)$$&#xa;$$f_{xy}=f(x+1,y)+f(x-1,y)+f(x,y+1)+f(x,y-1)-4f(x,y)$$&#xa;Substituting these for the partials in Euler equations above results in:&#xa;\begin{eqnarray*}&#xa;(E(x,y)-R(p,q))R_p &amp;=&amp; &#xa;\lambda(p(x,y+1)-2p(x,y)+p(x,y-1) - (q(x+1,y)+q(x-1,y)+q(x,y+1)+q(x,y-1)-4q(x,y))\\&#xa;(E(x,y)-R(p,q))R_q &amp;=&amp;&#xa;\lambda(q(x+1,y)-2q(x,y)+q(x-1,y) - (p(x+1,y)+p(x-1,y)+p(x,y+1)+p(x,y-1-4p(x,y))&#xa;\end{eqnarray*}"/>
</node>
<node CREATED="1166202855411" ID="Freemind_Link_155473703" MODIFIED="1166202857838" POSITION="right" TEXT="Problem 5"/>
